        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wilted spinach </strong>to the <strong>food processor</strong> with<strong> </strong>a <strong>third </strong>of your <strong>blanched peas </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Add your<strong> basil</strong>,<strong> peeled garlic </strong>and your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then blitz until well combined and smooth – this is your <strong>pea</strong> <strong>& basil pesto</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
